.:: Puzzle 3x7-Level-2-2::.
There are 7 different nationalities: british, canadian, colombian, egyptian, indian, japanese, thai
7 different games are played: poker, whist, billiard, snooker, bridge, domino, chess
The people use 7 different means of transport: bus, car, roller, scooter, ship, train, trike
 1. the canadian is on the right of the person driving the car##1
 2. the person playing bridge is the person playing bridge##1
 3. the person playing bridge is on the right of the person playing snooker##1
 4. the person playing snooker is on the left of the person driving the bus##1
 5. the person playing poker is the thai##1
 6. the british is the person driving the scooter##1
 7. the british is between the person playing chess and the person driving the trike##2
 8. the person playing billiard is on the left of the indian##1
 9. the person playing chess is on the left of the person playing snooker##1
10. the colombian is on the right of the person driving the ship##1
11. the indian is on the right of the british##1
12. the person driving the bus is the canadian##1
13. the egyptian is on the left of the british##1
14. the egyptian is on the right of the person driving the train##1
15. the canadian is on the far right##1
16. the person playing whist is on the left of the thai##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |     2     |      3       |    4     |   5    |     6     |    7     |
| Nationality   | japanese | thai      | egyptian     | british  | indian | colombian | canadian |
| Game         | whist  | poker | domino | billiard | chess | snooker   | bridge  |
| Transport     | roller   | train     | trike        | scooter  | ship   | car       | bus      |

